The world's largest hall lamp, listed in the Guinness World Records, has been lit up. The lamp in East China's Zhejiang Province has a history of more than 100 years and some of the craftsmanship has been lost.Photo: ChinanewsThe world's largest hall lamp, listed in the Guinness World Records, has been lit up. The lamp in East China's Zhejiang Province has a history of more than 100 years and some of the craftsmanship has been lost.With a height of 4.05 meters, a diameter of 2.10 meters and a weight of 127.5 kilograms, the hall lamp is inlaid with 400,000 glass beads. This magnificent hall lamp is extraordinarily bright and eye-catching after being lit."This hall lamp is hung every four years, usually from the Spring Festival to the Lantern Festival, for visitors to appreciate," said an administrator in charge of keeping the lamp, said that there are still more than 300 lamps of different sizes in the hall which are made of wood, bamboo, silk, glass, and even sheepskin.